org.soulwing.prospecto.api.meta

Interface MetadataHandler

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    LiteralMetadataHandler

    public interface MetadataHandler
    A handler for values associated with a MetaNode.

    An implementation of this class can produce and consume a metadata value associated with a view.

    Author:
    Carl Harris

    • Method Detail

      • produceValue

        Object produceValue(MetaNode node,
                  ViewContext context)
                    throws Exception
        Produces a value for the given node.

        This method is invoked during view generation. If the return value is null the metadata property will be included in the resulting view (but may be omitted by a writer). If the undefined value is returned, the metadata property will be excluded from the resulting view.

        Parameters:
        node - the subject node
        context - view context
        Returns:
        value which may be null or UndefinedValue.INSTANCE as noted above
        Throws:
        Exception

      • consumeValue

        void consumeValue(MetaNode node,
                Object value,
                ViewContext context)
                  throws Exception
        Consumes a value for the given node.

        This method is invoked during view application to allow the handler to use the value that was received in the input view in some manner.

        Parameters:
        node - the subject node
        value - input value (which may be null but will never be the UndefinedValue.INSTANCE
        context - view context
        Throws:
        Exception
